SIMPLE: sop
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sop
<hw>Sop</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>sop</ets>,
<ets>soppe</ets>; akin to AS. <ets>s<?/pan</ets> to sup, to sip, to
drink, D. <ets>sop</ets> sop, G. <ets>suppe</ets> soup, Icel.
<ets>soppa</ets> sop. See <er>Sup</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>, and cf.
<er>Soup</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Anything steeped, or dipped and
softened, in any liquid; especially, something dipped in broth or liquid
food, and intended to be eaten.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He it is to whom I shall give a <qex>sop</qex>, when I have dipped
it.</q> <rj><qau>John xiii. 26.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Sops</qex> in wine, quantity, inebriate more than wine
itself.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The bounded waters⟦br⟧
Should lift their bosoms higher than the shores,⟦br⟧
And make a <qex>sop</qex> of all this solid globe.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Anything given to pacify; -- so called from the sop
given to Cerberus, as related in mythology.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All nature is cured with a <qex>sop</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A thing of little or no value.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>P. Plowman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<cs><p><col><b>Sops in wine</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>an old name
of the clove pink, alluding to its having been used to flavor
wine.</cd>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Garlands of roses and <qex>sops in wine</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <col><b>Sops of wine</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>an old
European variety of apple, of a yellow and red color, shading to deep
red; -- called also <altname>sopsavine</altname>, and <altname>red
shropsavine</altname>.</cd>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p></cs>

<p><ent>Sop</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sop
<hw>Sop</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Sopped</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Sopping</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To steep or dip in any
liquid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sope</ent>⟦br⟧
